name: Navtara Veg Restaurant

reviews.review_text: The food was good. Coffee was great. Service given by staff Alomgir was very efficient.

I WOULD HAVE GIVEN  MINUS RATING IF AVAILABLE.

Pathetic service provider I have ever experienced . Cafe Bhosale was half shutter down so we went to this outlet of Navtara at around 10.25pm. My wife went to the loo. And we were seating to place the order but the waiter Ganesh was busy with the other customers. After some time Ganesh came to take the order, to start with we had ordered  paneer tikka masala and cheese stuffed garlic naan. But he said only plain naan is available as the bhatti is cold. Roti or chapati is available. Then we went to the cashier MR. NARESH WHO WAS VERY RUDE, MISLEADING AND OVERSMART on counter. Requested him to give managers contact number as we were disappointed with the service. The cashier said he doesn't have managers number. Then I saw the managers number on no smoking board, called him and explained him the entire scenario.

IT WAS NOT ABOUT THE FOOD BUT ABOUT THE COMMUNICATION, BEHAVIOUR, HOSPITALITY TOWARDS THE CUSTOMER.

NAVTARA HOTEL CHAINS THIS PORVORIM OUTLET IS THE WORST. WE HAD ALSO ENJOYED OUR MEAL IN THE OTHER OUTLETS WHICH WERE GOOD.

THIS OUTLET OF NAVTARA NEEDS TO BE IMPROVED IN THEIR SERVICE STAFF ESPECIALLY MR. NARESH WHO SEATS ON THE COUNTER.

Worst service ever.
They will never agree to their fault.
Don't go here.
Because of them we have wasted so much food.

description:
### Navtara Veg Restaurant: A Taste of Goa with a Touch of South India

Nestled within the vibrant culinary landscape of Goa, **Navtara Veg Restaurant** boasts an overall rating of **4.1** from over **9,580 diners**, highlighting its popularity and appeal. Customers frequently rave about its exceptional **South Indian food** (103 mentions), with **pav bhaji** (39 mentions), and **puri bhaji** (26 mentions) touted as standout offerings. Despite the praises for its culinary delights, the restaurant has faced some criticism regarding its service, underscoring the duality of the dining experience here.

### Ambiance & Design

The images captured by patrons reveal a cozy atmosphere that reflects a welcoming yet straightforward dining space. Simple decor paired with ambient lighting creates a casual dining environment suitable for families and friends alike. While no specific comments about music were highlighted, the ambiance appears to facilitate a relaxed, conversational setting, perfect for enjoying a lingering meal.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

Navtara’s menu shines with **signature South Indian dishes**. Diners frequently commend the incredible **coffee**—a standout in customers' reviews—as well as the flavorful **paneer tikka masala** and **cheese-stuffed garlic naan**. The presentation of dishes, while likely utilitarian, speaks to the flavors and freshness typical of popular South Indian cuisine. Vegetarian patrons will find plenty of options that cater to their preferences, making it a go-to spot for plant-based dining.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer experiences at Navtara Veg Restaurant vary widely, with some diners praising the food but expressing significant concern over the service. One reviewer highlighted an **efficient service** from a staff member named Alomgir, showcasing that positive experiences are indeed possible. However, counterpointed by several negative reviews, many customers specifically criticized the **staff's efficiency and communication**, portraying a disconcerting pattern of poor service. 

One particularly scathing review described the service as "pathetic," detailing an encounter with an unhelpful cashier named Mr. Naresh and an overall disappointing visit due to delays and a lack of attentiveness from the staff. Such mixed sentiments reflect a pressing need for improvements in the service department, particularly regarding staff responsiveness and hospitality.

### Popularity & Reviews

Despite its mixed reviews, Navtara has cultivated a loyal customer base keen on returning to enjoy its menu offerings. Social media buzz reflects a duality where culinary experience often contrasts with service reviews, hence, customers may find the allure of the food behind their reservations about the overall experience. It remains worth noting that some diners still appreciate Navtara enough to extol its virtues, suggesting that with the right attention to service quality, it could elevate its standing further.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The collection of photographs shared by customers showcases mouth-watering dishes that highlight the vibrancy of the cuisine offered at Navtara. From beautifully plated **pav bhaji** to steaming cups of coffee, these visuals evoke the flavorful experiences many seek. The images also evoke a sense of warmth in the dining space, echoing the casual yet inviting environment.

### Conclusion

In summary, **Navtara Veg Restaurant** presents a compelling option for anyone exploring authentic **South Indian cuisine** in Goa. While the food, characterized by flavor and authenticity, earns high marks, customer experiences reveal a pressing need for service improvement. For those willing to navigate the occasional hiccup in service, a satisfaction guaranteed comes from the delightful and extensive vegetarian menu that remains a favorite in the area. With an eye towards enhancing guest relations, Navtara could truly solidify its place as a must-visit in Goa’s diverse culinary scene.
